{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"@property"},{"kind":"text","text":" ("},{"kind":"keyword","text":"nonatomic"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:d","text":"double"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"zoomLevel"},{"kind":"text","text":";"}],"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["occ"]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In addition to affecting the visual size and detail of features on the map,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the zoom level affects the size of the vector tiles that are loaded. At zoom"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"level 0, each tile covers the entire world map; at zoom level 1, it covers ¼"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of the world; at zoom level 2, "},{"type":"text","text":"1"},{"type":"text","text":"⁄"},{"type":"text","text":"16"},{"type":"text","text":" of the world, and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"so on."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Changing the value of this property updates the map view immediately. If you"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"want to animate the change, use the "},{"code":"-setZoomLevel:animated:","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" method instead."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView"]]},"sections":[],"metadata":{"symbolKind":"property","modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"title":"zoomLevel","externalID":"c:objc(cs)MLNMapView(py)zoomLevel","roleHeading":"Instance Property","remoteSource":{"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/maplibre\/maplibre-native\/blob\/main\/platform\/ios\/src\/MLNMapView.h#L1026","fileName":"MLNMapView.h"},"fra